# NP-completeness

[NP-completeness](/NP-completeness) is a foundational concept in the field of computational complexity theory, a branch of theoretical computer science that deals with the resources required to solve computational problems. It's the point where problems become so difficult to solve that we start questioning the very nature of computation itself. Think of it as the mathematical equivalent of staring into an abyss and realizing it’s staring back, unimpressed.

